bug.short_desc: Fix the Generics related warnings in official build

long_desc.thetext:
Ref to bug 421017, which introduces generics to jdt.core project via compliance level 1_6. Even though we had disabled the warnings in the pref file, the official build still enables them, as a result of which we get warnings in the build:
http://download.eclipse.org/eclipse/downloads/drops4/N20131128-2000/compilelogs/plugins/org.eclipse.jdt.core_3.10.0.N20131128-2000/@dot.html
We have to generify them where ever possible or suppress otherwise. For all APIs we will suppress the warnings and other cases need to be looked at case-by-case.

Interestingly, I see many more warnings in my local environment (in thousands). But the official build seem to complain only of those inside org.eclipse.jdt.core/antadapter. I have no idea why.
Looking at the thousand of warning to deal with, I suggest we just suppress all the warning and can take up the generifying task whenever we get opportunity in a incremental manner.

Looks like hundreds of files to be touched and too bad we don't have a quick fix to apply at the class to address multiple warnings.
Dani, is there a chance the bug 418593 will be taken up by during M4? :)

Created attachment 237893 Patch
This patch sets the pref for raw type and unchecked to 'warning' in org.eclipse.jdt.core. More importantly, where ever required, I have added @SuppressWarnings to get rid of the warnings.

Created attachment 237902 Updated patch
In this patch, I Have also addressed couple of resource leak warnings.

Created attachment 237906 Updated patch
Disabled the unavoidable generic problems reporting to match what we have in the build environment.
